    "created_at": "2016-03-04T15:52:52Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-03-04T15:52:52Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Let's not do that: The tests would no longer be hermetic and require reasoning about a bunch of infrastructure to fix any bug. The result will be some flaky tests that nobody ever does anything about, stalling development at random times, or encouraging people to ignore any other failures. \n\nWe've been there, it was bad, let's not do it again.\n\nI'd rather remove 'make tests' entirely than deal with adding more infrastructure that this team needs to support: we're overburdened there as it is.\n\nIf needing python for a test feels overburdensome, the following remedies could work:\n- check for the presence (or absence) of the necessary Python interpreter, and if it doesn't exist, print a bunch of lines of warning and exit with success\n- rewrite the servers in C (much easier once #5383 goes in)\n"
  },
